		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">koitsu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Expect the service to become trash in about 5 years.</div><br /><br />Honestly, I can't think of anyone better at handling this service than Microsoft. They have both the skill, the means, and the experience. The &quot;worst&quot; thing that can happen is assimilating it into a superior service.<br />MS themselves switched to Git years ago despite having their own source control (TFVC), and have been using GitHub for most of their open source projects, despite having provided CodePlex for others. Expect most developers inside Microsoft to be big proponents of GitHub with a genuine interest to see it remain a functional platform.

		

